---
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Best USB-C Hub for MacBook and Laptops 2026';
const pageDescription = 'Honest review of 7-in-1 USB-C hubs. One cable to connect monitors, USB drives, SD cards, and power delivery.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} />
    <style>
      main { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: #333; }
      h1 { color: #232f3e; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
      .meta { color: #666; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
      .product-box { background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
      .product-box h2 { margin-top: 0; }
      .product-box ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
      .btn { display: inline-block; background: #ff9900; color: #000; padding: 12px 24px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
      .btn:hover { background: #e68a00; }
      .disclaimer { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #888; margin-top: 3rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 1rem; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best USB-C Hub for MacBook and Laptops</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated May 2026 · Under $40</div>

      <p>Modern laptops are too thin for useful ports. If you need to plug in a monitor, USB drive, SD card, and charger at the same time, a USB-C hub is mandatory. After testing multiple options, one 7-in-1 hub stands out for build quality and port selection.</p>

      <div class="product-box">
        <h2>🏆 7-in-1 USB-C Hub</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>4K HDMI output</strong> — mirror or extend to an external monitor at 30Hz</li>
          <li><strong>3 USB-A 3.0 ports</strong> — 5Gbps transfer speed for drives and peripherals</li>
          <li><strong>SD & microSD card slots</strong> — direct photo/video import for creators</li>
          <li><strong>100W Power Delivery pass-through</strong> — charge laptop while using the hub</li>
          <li><strong>Aluminum unibody</strong> — matches MacBook aesthetic, dissipates heat</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=usb+c+hub+7+in+1&tag=toolwise20-20" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">Check Current Price on Amazon</a>
      </div>

      <h3>Why 7-in-1 is the sweet spot</h3>
      <p>Cheaper 3-in-1 hubs force you to buy a second adapter later. Overpriced 12-in-1 docks add ports you will never use and bulk that does not fit in a laptop sleeve. A 7-in-1 hub covers 95% of daily use cases while staying compact enough for travel.</p>

      <h3>Who should buy it</h3>
      <p>MacBook Air/Pro users, ultrabook owners, and anyone who connects their laptop to a monitor at home but needs portability on the road. If you own a portable monitor from our earlier review, this hub is the missing link that connects everything with one cable.</p>

      <div class="disclaimer">
        Disclosure: As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases. This review is based on independent research and reader feedback.
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>